biography:

_This is what Florian says:_

I am a Data Scientist living in Cologne, Germany with a mathematical background. 
After my postdoctoral position I started as a Data Scientist at [Blue Yonder](http://www.blue-yonder.com/),
the leading platform provider for Predictive Applications and Big Data in the European market.
Right now I enjoy working on innovative Data Science projects with experts every day at [inovex](https://www.inovex.de/en/). With more than five years of project experience in the field of Predictive & Prescriptive Analytics and Big Data, I have acquired profound knowledge in the domains of mathematical modelling, statistics, machine learning, high-performance computing and data mining.

For the last years I programmed mostly with the Python Data Science stack ([NumPy](http://www.numpy.org/), [SciPy](http://www.scipy.org/), [Scikit-Learn](http://scikit-learn.org/), [Pandas](http://pandas.pydata.org/), [Matplotlib](http://matplotlib.org/), [Jupyter](http://jupyter.org/), etc.) to which I also contributed several extensions.
